penske still wears those crisp white shirts
you_know the work_ethic the go it_really hasn_t changed said rick_mears who won four of team_penske s record 17 indy 500s
the love affair actually began in_1951 when penske s father jay brought his_son to the fabled speedway for the first_time
but the young penske was mesmerized by the speed and sound his interest_in all things auto_racing solidified that afternoon
i remember we sat down_off the fourth turn and could hardly see the cars go by penske_said this_week and i_guess at that point i_was injected with motor racing and really wanted_to drive here
penske_began to carve out his name in lower tier series and he_was even offered a rookie test at_indianapolis
but penske s father had always encouraged him to_be an entrepreneur and the business side of the sport was_just as appealing
so_when he turned down the test and a young italian named mario_andretti took it instead_penske s career began_to change course
he soon retired from driving to focus_on his successful car_dealerships and in 1965 launched penske_racing at the 24_hours of daytona
instead_penske turned to him and said well just don_t stick it in the_fence
but little did mears know penske had_his eye on the young hotshot driver and would hire him to_drive the_following year

donohue was killed in 1975 while practicing for a formula_one race and penske would shutter his f1_team a_couple of years later
and the open_wheel split that jeopardized the very existence of the indianapolis_500 kept penske from competing in 1996_2000
probably one of the_biggest mistakes i_made in racing penske_said
penske_won his_first year back to the_brickyard ushering in a new era_of sustained success that extends far beyond indycar
